The paper deals with the problem of tracking objects in videos, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO). The paper also proposes a new methodology for analyzing and comparing different tracking methods, which involves machine learning techniques (cs.LG) and multimedia processing (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper presents an open source system for practical tracking requirements, which involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
